Docker commands:

How to show Running/stop state Containers:
To show Running state containers
> docker ps
To show all running and accidently stopped containers
> docker ps -a
How to stop containers 
> docker stop container_name
> docker ps -a

Rm - Remove a Container 
> docker rm <container-ID>

Rmi- Remove a Image
How to check docker images
> docker images
> docker rmi image name or ID

Pull- Download an Image
> docker pull image name

Run an Instance of Docker Container
> docker run image name or container name

Sleep container for some time
> docker run container-name sleep 5

Exec- Execute a command
> docker ps -a
> docker exec run <options>
    options:
        to go inside container and execute some commands
        > /bin/bash 

        To show some contents host file information
        > cat /etc/hosts

Run - attach and detach
> docker run kodekloud/simple-webapp
> docker attach <container-ID>
Run docker in background
> docker run -d


Exercises:
> docker run centos
> docker pull centos
> docker run -it centos bash
> cat /etc/*release*
> exit


Run - PORT Mapping
> docker run -p 80:5000 <container name>

and access it with IP 
http://192.168.1.5:80


RUN- Volume Mapping
> docker run mysql
> docker run -v /opt/datadir:/var/lib/mysql mysql
    /opt/datadir - Is external volume and /var/lib/mysql is container volume

Inspect Container
> docker inspect <container ID>

Container Logs
> docker logs <container ID>

Print every second
> docker run timer

How to run in backgroung mode
> docker run -d timer
> docker ps
> docker attach <container ID>


Pull Jenkins image
> docker run jenkins
> docker run -p 8080:8080 jenkins


Dependencies: apt-get update && apt-get install -y python python-setuptools python-dev build-essential python-pip python-mysqldb

Build Docker commands:

> docker build .
> docker build . -t my_simple_webapp



Command vs Entrypoint
Command 
> docker run <container ID> sleep 10

Entrypoint
FROM XYZ
CMD sleep 10
